<h2>Synopsis</h2>

<p>
An expedition to the far north.  
A bunker buried beneath the ice.  
A project designed to preserve life.
</p>

<p>
Selected to collaborate with the Borealis Garden Initiative, a team of 
scientists and specialists travels to a remote Arctic station dedicated 
to safeguarding plant life for the future of humanity.
</p>

<p>
The mission seems routine. Document, evaluate, and return.
</p>

<p>
But upon arrival, nothing is quite as expected.
</p>

<p>
Equipment out of place.  
Deteriorating facilities.  
Incomplete records.  
Silences that shouldn't exist.
</p>

<p>
As isolation deepens, the expedition begins to face a series of unsettling 
events that defy logical explanation.
</p>

<p>
What started as a scientific mission soon becomes a struggle to understand 
what happened at Borealis… and whether they are truly alone.
</p>

<p>
<b>Beyond Borealis</b> is a psychological survival thriller about isolation, 
uncertainty, and the boundaries of the unknown.
</p>
